Renders a focused LLM repair prompt for a service file that has a high
percentage of stub/placeholder functions.  Provides related model, schema,
and router context to guide the LLM toward correct SQLAlchemy 2.x async
ORM implementations.

Template Variables:
- svc_path: Relative path to the service file being repaired
- pct: Percentage of stub functions in the service file (float)
- context_block: Multi-file context block (service + related files concatenated)
- spec_context: Optional spec/data-model context string (may be empty)
- related_model: Content of the related ORM model file (may be empty)
- related_schema: Content of the related Pydantic schema file (may be empty)
- related_router: Content of the related FastAPI router file (may be empty)
#}
The service file "{{ svc_path }}" has {{ pct }}% placeholder stub functions.
Replace every stub function with a real SQLAlchemy 2.x async ORM implementation.

Requirements:
- Use `await session.execute(select(Model).where(...))` for queries
- Use `await session.execute(insert(Model).values(...).returning(Model))` for inserts
- Use `await session.execute(update(Model).where(...).values(...).returning(Model))` for updates
- Use `await session.execute(delete(Model).where(...))` for deletes
- Always `await session.commit()` after mutating operations
- Handle `scalar_one_or_none()` / `scalars().all()` for result extraction
- Return typed objects matching the schema, not raw dicts

